{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-template-js","path":"/pages/sports","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"da30b4c9-e9b9-57bb-9f72-d32c9cebbab4","html":"<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/c58a3/jadwin.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 33.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source srcset=\"/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/8ac56/jadwin.webp 240w,\n/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/d3be9/jadwin.webp 480w,\n/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/e46b2/jadwin.webp 960w,\n/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/f992d/jadwin.webp 1440w,\n/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/293e0/jadwin.webp 1500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/webp\">\n          <source srcset=\"/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/09b79/jadwin.jpg 240w,\n/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/7cc5e/jadwin.jpg 480w,\n/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/6a068/jadwin.jpg 960w,\n/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/644c5/jadwin.jpg 1440w,\n/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/c58a3/jadwin.jpg 1500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" type=\"image/jpeg\">\n          <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" src=\"/static/42e42808731f7fe99c8ced7ce1d13ecb/6a068/jadwin.jpg\" alt=\"      static media jadwin\" title=\"      static media jadwin\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\">\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<p>I have extensive experience in sportswriting, often informed by a quantitative perspective and firsthand statistical analysis. You can see <a href=\"/tag/sports/\">a few recent blog posts on sports here</a> and some of my favorite writing below.</p>\n<h4 id=\"mit-sloan-sports-analytics-conference-2013\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#mit-sloan-sports-analytics-conference-2013\" aria-label=\"mit sloan sports analytics conference 2013 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>MIT Sloan Sports Analytics Conference (2013)</h4>\n<p>My research paper, “Does a ‘coattail effect’ influence the valuation of players in the Major League Baseball draft?”, was accepted for publication and a poster at the 2013 MIT Sloan Sports Analytics Conference. <a href=\"/media/Kevin_Whitaker_SSAC_2013.pdf\">You can read the paper here</a>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"risk-preferences-and-wage-determination-in-mlb-2013\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#risk-preferences-and-wage-determination-in-mlb-2013\" aria-label=\"risk preferences and wage determination in mlb 2013 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Risk Preferences and Wage Determination in MLB (2013)</h4>\n<p>My Princeton senior thesis, “Risk Preferences and Wage Determination in the Major League Baseball Labor Market,” empirically studied the impact of volatility on players’ salaries in free agency. Using a sample of 1,599 contracts signed from 1993-2012, MLB teams were found to pay a premium for players with more volatility, indicating that they are risk-seeking, but only for short-term contracts. <a href=\"/media/THESIS-FINAL.pdf\">You can read the paper here</a>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"princeton-alumni-weekly-2010-20\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#princeton-alumni-weekly-2010-20\" aria-label=\"princeton alumni weekly 2010 20 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Princeton Alumni Weekly (2010-20)</h4>\n<p>I was a student contributor to PAW from 2011-13 writing weekly columns and regular magazine features on Princeton sports, and have since then occasionally contributed articles on Princeton football and basketball. You can find <a href=\"https://paw.princeton.edu/search/site/%2522By%2520Kevin%2520Whitaker%2520%25E2%2580%259913%2522\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">my author archive here</a> and some recent or favorite articles below: </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://paw.princeton.edu/article/football-dartmouth-topples-princeton-unbeaten-battle-yankee-stadium\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Dartmouth topples Princeton in unbeaten battle at Yankee Stadium</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://paw.princeton.edu/article/womens-basketball-dancing-again\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Dancing again</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://paw.princeton.edu/article/don%E2%80%99t-fear-ivy-league-tournament\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Don’t fear the Ivy League Tournament</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://paw.princeton.edu/article/comeback-princeton-football-stuns-harvard-39-34\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The comeback: Princeton football stuns Harvard, 39-34</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"nyc-buckets-2014-18\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#nyc-buckets-2014-18\" aria-label=\"nyc buckets 2014 18 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>NYC Buckets (2014-18)</h4>\n<p>I wrote a weekly column about Ivy League Basketball, covered games from various mid-major conferences, and wrote occasional analysis features for NYC Buckets, a website covering college basketball around the Northeast. The website has since disbanded but some of my favorite evergreen articles are saved here: </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/chart-shots/you-can-take-the-players-out-of-new-york-city-but-fb2386050d75\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">You can take the players out of New York City, But…</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/chart-shots/the-long-arc-of-home-court-advantage-dc54c591bb7f\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The long arc of home-court advantage</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/chart-shots/the-shotties-miscellaneous-ivy-league-awards-406a3deca259\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">The Shotties: Detailed shot charts</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/chart-shots/evaluating-preseason-college-basketball-projections-eccbb34345fd\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Evaluating preseason college basketball projections</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/chart-shots/how-scorekeeper-biases-affect-shot-selection-data-987915423538\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">How scorekeeper biases affect shot-selection data</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"baseball-prospectus-2013-14\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#baseball-prospectus-2013-14\" aria-label=\"baseball prospectus 2013 14 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Baseball Prospectus (2013-14)</h4>\n<p>I wrote two guest articles for Baseball Prospectus: </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.baseballprospectus.com/prospects/article/23795/baseball-proguestus-riding-top-prospects-coattails-in-the-mlb-draft/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Riding top prospects’ coattails in the MLB Draft</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.baseballprospectus.com/news/article/22497/baseball-proguestus-rethinking-hall-of-fame-standards-in-expansion-eras/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Rethinking Hall of Fame standards in expansion eras</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"the-daily-princetonian-2009-13\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-daily-princetonian-2009-13\" aria-label=\"the daily princetonian 2009 13 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Daily Princetonian (2009-13)</h4>\n<p>I was the Executive Editor for Sports for two years, in which I managed a staff of about 20 writers, created and assigned story ideas, coordinated with other sections, and wrote articles and columns. I also worked as a columnist, senior writer, and staff photographer for the sports section before and after my time as editor. </p>\n<h4 id=\"sports-illustrated-2012\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#sports-illustrated-2012\" aria-label=\"sports illustrated 2012 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sports Illustrated (2012)</h4>\n<p>I was an editorial intern at Sports Illustrated in 2012, doing research and fact-checking for magazine articles and writing for a special issue on college football. </p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Sportswriting and analysis","date":null,"description":null,"socialImage":"../../static/media/jadwin.jpg"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/pages/sports"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}